programme.desc: An ordinary day in Green Park begins with Eve helping Will to cheat on his homework and Abe teaching Eve the importance of `dares'. But then Will's mum, Rebecca, arrives from Dubai. programme.title: Eve
programme.desc: With Mr Gwenlan on the loose, Katherine wants Eve to be locked up at Calimov. Eve and Nick talk her out of it as long as Eve stays out of trouble. Yet when Eve offers to babysit Zoe, Lily's tearaway cousin, staying out of trouble seems wholly unlikely. To understand the behaviour of 'small humans' Eve lets Zoe run riot in the local park. Zoe gets bored, and with Abe's advice, Eve lets Zoe eat as many ice creams as she wants. Things get messy and Will and Lily aren't impressed. But as Eve promises to impose a strict new regime on young Zoe, Will wants to give Eve a second chance. Katherine is less interested in second chances and when she realises that Mr Gwenlan stole a spiderbot from Calimov she's determined that Eve be kept under lock and key. Meanwhile, Zoe rebels against Eve and runs away. The gang can't find her anywhere. By the time Nick and Katherine arrive to check up on Eve, all's well and Eve is the picture of innocence. If only the same could be true of Abe, whose plan to avoid household chores backfires spectacularly.(n)

programme.title: Eve
programme.desc: Eve feels compelled to try out a youth group called PARTY, and drags her friends along to its lakeside activities. Eve loves PARTY and its youth leader is impressed by Eve's attitude to technology. But when Eve becomes obsessed with the idea of canoeing on the lake Will starts to get really nervous. Nick and Zac have worries of their own and attempt to listen into Mr Gwenlan's phone calls. When Mr Gwenlan turns out to be PARTY's co-founder and appears at the youth club, Will marches Eve home. Will can't understand why Eve's protocols aren't responding to danger and has strong words with Eve but she storms off. Will, Lily and Zac reach the lakeside in time to find the youth group encouraging Eve to cross the lake on a rickety raft. If Eve falls in, it would be the end of her.
